Reliance Industries May Face 15 Billion Rupee Fine, Times Says

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-02-14T05:36:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/reliance-industries-may-face-15-billion-rupee-fine-times-says.html
  India ’s stock market regulator may
fine  Reliance Industries Ltd . 15 billion rupees ($330 million)
in an insider trading case, the Economic Times reported, citing
an unidentified person close to the proceedings.  Reliance Industries, which made a profit of 5 billion
rupees from the sale of a stake in Reliance Petroleum Ltd., is
trying to settle the case through plea bargaining or a consent
order in which guilt is neither admitted or denied, the
newspaper said.  There is no certainty that the 15 billion rupee penalty
will be imposed, according to the report. Fines for insider
trading have ranged from a few hundred thousand rupees to 20
million rupees, the Economic Times said.  Manoj Warrier, a spokesman for Reliance Industries, India’s
biggest company by market value, declined to comment on the
report. N. Hariharan, a spokesman for the  Securities and
Exchange Board of India , declined to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
